                                gadgets. There are several implementations based...</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                    <article>
                        <img class="w-full rounded" src="https://via.placeholder.com/384x223/4e9c6d/ffffff?text=Video+2" alt="" data-modalpreview="modal-preview" data-video="f24WPDYjz8o">
                        <div class="mt-1 flex flex-col gap-4">
                            <time class="text-sm font-bold text-coral-red-500">August 5, 2022</time>
                            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold leading-8 text-white">I’ll be at the next VidCon 2022 in Tokyo unveiling new and exciting gadgets!</h2>
                            <p class="leading-7 text-gray-400">A gadget is a mechanical device or any ingenious article. Gadgets are sometimes referred to as gizmos. In the software industry, “Gadget” refers to computer programs that provide services
                                without needing an independent application to be launched for each one, but instead run in an environment that manages multiple gadgets. There are several implementations based...</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                    <article>
                        <img class="w-full rounded" src="https://via.placeholder.com/384x223/ff0000/ffffff?text=Video+3" alt="" data-modalpreview="modal-preview" data-video="6Q7tdD5lJxg">
                        <div class="mt-1 flex flex-col gap-4">
                            <time class="text-sm font-bold text-coral-red-500">August 5, 2022</time>
                            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold leading-8 text-white">I’ll be at the next VidCon 2022 in Tokyo unveiling new and exciting gadgets!</h2>
                            <p class="leading-7 text-gray-400">In the software industry, “Gadget” refers to computer programs that provide services without needing an independent application to be launched for each one, but instead run in an
                                environment that manages multiple gadgets. There are several implementations based...</p>
                        </div>
                    </article>
                {% endfor %}
            </div>

            <div class="mt-16 flex justify-center">
                <button class="max-w-fit self-center px-6 text-center font-bold uppercase text-white transition bg-coral-red-500 py-3.5 hover:bg-coral-red-700">Load more</button>
            </div>
        </section>

        <div aria-hidden="true" class="invisible fixed top-0 left-0 z-20 flex h-screen w-screen flex-col items-center justify-center opacity-0 transition duration-500" id="modal-preview">
            <iframe class="z-20 aspect-video w-full max-w-screen-lg" id="iframeVideo" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
    </main>
{% endblock %}
